         Asset Management,&nbspProduct Manager: currently 94 jobs.The latest job was posted on 25 Jul 17.
Asset Management - Product Manager
Asset management is about selecting and monitoring the right investments for clients. A product manager in asset management provides insights into multi-asset portfolio characteristics, usage and calculations. Working with the asset management team, a product manager is required to plan, co-ordinate, manage, optimize and report the funds. A product manager reviews the right communication materials for accuracy and collaborates with various business areas to understand and address relevant issues. You can easily browse through the jobs on offer for a product manager role in asset management on efinancialcareers.com. A bachelor’s degree is a minimum for the profile. The skills required for this job include – good verbal and written communication, ability to coordinate with different teams and deliver projects on time and strong attention to detail
New York City offers ample opportunities in this role, where you can work for organizations such as BlackRock. However, this does not mean that there aren’t options available elsewhere in North America. StateStreet and Fidelity in Boston, PIMCO in California and Vanguard in Pennsylvania are some of the major players spread across the continent.
Apart from the mentioned opportunities in North America, England, Italy, Ireland, Japan, Switzerland, and Singapore are all convenient markets for product manager jobs and others in the asset management market.





