Asset Management - Product & Fund Delivery Manager - Associate - Senningerberg, L | JPMorgan Chase & Co.































































Careers / Job Search / Job Details





















Apply Now
               

Refer a Friend






Asset Management - Product & Fund Delivery Manager - Associate

Req #: 170065843
Location:


Senningerberg, 
		L,
                LU

Job Category: Asset Management
Potential Referral Amount: 4000 Euro (EUR)


JPMorgan Chase & Co. is a leading global financial services firm with assets of more than $2.4 trillion, over 240,000 employees and operations in over 60 countries. It operates across four business segments including Asset & Wealth Management, Corporate and Investment Banking, Commercial Banking and Consumer and Community Banking. 

J.P. Morgan Asset & Wealth Management is made up of the Asset Management and Wealth Management

 
The Team 
Luxembourg Product & Fund Delivery is the centre of expertise and knowledge for implementation of any fund initiatives in the JPMorgan Asset Management Luxembourg proprietary fund range: new fund and share class launches, liquidations, mergers, enhancements to existing funds, local coordination all affected stakeholders in Luxembourg. We operate in partnership with the investment managers and our core focus is on those activities performed in Luxembourg: Transfer Agency, Fund Accounting, Custody, Management Company, Audit, and general oversight of delegated matters with Luxembourg stakeholders. The team is made of experienced product & project managers.
 
Main Responsibilities & Duties

The primary responsibility will be the efficient project management of initiatives that seek to deliver new products or enhance the existing product range. The typical type of product initiatives managed by the team are: investment fund launches, liquidations, mergers, any changes/enhancements to existing products, manage the implementation of any changes driven by prospectus updates and regulations, share class activations on behalf of Sales and Distribution.

Typically, new product initiatives follow several phases: i) idea generation, ii) pre-scoping, iii) scoping, iv) implementation, v) hand over to teams in Operations Dpt and vi) go live or execution.

Example of project: launch of the JPMorgan China A-Share Opportunities Fund: 


The product delivery manager will have various degrees of involvement in the phases ii) to vi).

A complex product such as this fund will require the product delivery manager to feed the Product Development team with critical operational information that is required during the pre-scoping and scoping phases i.e. can the new product idea be supported by the operational teams and if not, what are the initial solutions envisaged to make it happen. How can we develop a robust and scalable process to handle an increased volume of new OTC derivative instruments, until IT enhancements are made? Will the regulatory context require special attention to the legal agreements in place? Any market specificities such as Stock Connect or RQFII that need to be analysed at pre-scoping phase?

The product delivery manager will then focus on the implementation and launch in partnership with operational areas located in Luxembourg, working together with external and internal parties such as the Transfer Agency, Fund Accounting, Auditors, as appropriate, and it will include analysis work with the Funds Control team, and the Management Company’s Conducting Officers. This is a project and delivery work performed in cooperation with the Product Development and Product Delivery teams in London and in Asia. The fund delivery manager will chair meetings and working groups locally in Luxembourg

In the context of the JPMAM Luxembourg fund range and UCITS5, the product delivery manager responsibilities include:


Utilize best practices in terms of project management (score cards, project dash boards, issue log, executive management reporting, etc). The product delivery manager is responsible for a portfolio of projects.

Removes obstacles that prevent the delivery of product solutions; acts immediately to address problems or potential problems, and seize opportunities.

Employs partnership skills and leverage subject matter experts (internally and externally) to effectively deliver the fund project. Develop/maintain long-term relationships with Fund accountants, Custodians, Auditors, Transfer Agents etc.) and internal business partners (Product Development, Risk Management, Internal Audit, Compliance, Legal, Tax, etc.)

Facilitate a governance process aiming at supporting all tasks required to ensure smooth project delivery.

Define and document the service structure, prepare Service Level Agreements, operating memorandums, and relevant workflows for the business process.

Required  Experience


The candidate must be familiar with Luxembourg and Irish collective investment schemes (ie UCITS5, AIFMD) and their associated end-to-end processes as well as having a broad knowledge of operational, financial, tax and regulatory requirements in multiple jurisdictions where the funds invest or are distributed. The candidate needs to have a solid ETF background, be open to challenges and have a critical and risk mindset.

Typically the candidate needs to have experience in the ETF business, as product specialist or implementation manager or auditor.

 Required Skills


Project Management Skills and ability to work independently/ be self driven

Excellent interpersonal and problem solving skills

Strong team player

Leadership and relationship management skills

Sense of Innovation and ability to deliver

Strong communication and information sharing skills

Negotiation and influencing skills

Ability to multi-task and work under pressure

Positive attitude towards compliance and controls
 
JPMorgan offers an exceptional benefits program and a highly competitive compensation package. JPMorgan is an Equal Opportunity Employer.  


